              <h2>1. Degree (commerce)</h2>
              <p>Now a day’s students are preferring commerce to science. As commerce gives same number of career opportunities as that of the science. Commerce students have great career options when it comes to graduation.</p>
              <b>-B. Com </b>Bachelor of commerce is a graduation course where you will be able to complete your higher studies with commerce subjects <br>
              <b>-B.B.M</b>Bachelor of Business Management
                It is a 3-year Degree course. Many MNCs recruit skilled B.B.A. graduates for management and finance related posts <br>
              <b>-C.A</b>Chartered Accountant
                It is to handle the financial affairs of businesses and companies in accordance with the laws set by Government authorities. <br>
              <b>-Law </b>Earlier, only Graduates were allowed to pursue L.L.B. But, new rules, states it is also possible for 12th Commerce students to pursue Law course from Law schools after schooling. <br>
              <b>-B.H.M</b>Bachelor of Hotel Management.
                It has got elements of the hospitality sector. But, degree course in Hotel Management is more valuable than the hospitality diploma courses <br>
              </p>
    
